# Inbox Flow — Product Spec

Brand: **Inbox Flow** · Domain: **inboxflow.io** · Style: dark-first professional desktop + TUI mode.

When implementing or changing features, follow these sections exactly.

## SMTP Manager

Build a professional SMTP management system (dedicated page under Settings / SMTP).

Users must be able to:

- Add unlimited SMTP servers
- Edit SMTP servers
- Delete SMTP servers
- Enable or disable SMTP servers
- Organize SMTP servers with labels
- Test SMTP connection before saving
- Verify SMTP authentication
- Display connection status: `Connected` | `Failed` | `Pending`
- Show detailed error messages if authentication fails
- Automatically detect common SMTP configuration issues
- Support presets: Amazon SES SMTP, Mailgun SMTP, SendGrid SMTP, Postmark SMTP, Gmail SMTP, Outlook SMTP, Zoho SMTP, Custom SMTP
- **SMTP rotation** across active accounts: `round_robin` | `weighted` | `failover`, respecting daily/hourly limits (load distribution + reliability — not policy evasion)

Each SMTP profile supports:

- Host, Port, Username, Password
- Encryption: SSL / TLS / STARTTLS
- Sender Name, Sender Email, Reply-To Email
- Daily Sending Limit, Hourly Limit, Priority, Notes

Include a **Test Connection** button that performs a **real** SMTP `verify()` (and optional test send) before the profile can be marked **active**. Default SMTP accounts use 465↔587 port failover.

## Intelligent Sending Queue

Never send all emails simultaneously.

User-configurable:

- Batch Size (default 10–20)
- Delay Between Batches (default 3–10s)
- Delay Between Individual Emails (default ~500ms)
- Maximum Concurrent Connections
- Maximum Emails Per Minute
- Maximum Emails Per Hour

Flow: send batch → wait → next batch → until complete.

Queue must support:

- Pause Campaign
- Resume Campaign
- Cancel Campaign
- Retry Failed Emails
- Skip Invalid Emails
- Queue Priority
- Live Progress UI: bar, sent/total, success, failed, remaining, ETA, live speed

## HTML Campaign Import

Users can import complete HTML email templates.

Formats: HTML files, ZIP files, MJML, drag-and-drop upload.

Importer must:

- Detect images, upload/store assets, fix relative paths
- Generate plain-text when possible
- Validate HTML for email compatibility
- Flag unsupported HTML/CSS
- Warn about render/deliverability risks

After import: edit in visual builder **or** HTML source.

## Professional Desktop-Style Interface

Look like desktop software (VS Code, Postman, Docker Desktop, GitHub Desktop, Raycast, Warp, Linear, Notion Desktop) — not a marketing website.

Required:

- Dark-first design
- Multi-panel layout
- Resizable sidebars
- Command palette (Ctrl/Cmd + K)
- Keyboard shortcuts
- Tabbed workspace
- Dockable / toggle panels
- Activity sidebar
- Status bar
- Notification center
- Smooth animations, professional mono typography
- Minimal modern UI, high-performance rendering

Keep CRT/TUI phosphor accents; square corners; no purple SaaS gradients.

## Terminal (TUI) Mode

Integrated terminal-style log console for advanced users.

Show live:

- Campaign logs, SMTP connection logs, queue activity
- Delivery / bounce / auth / error logs
- Real-time system events

Terminal supports: color-coded levels, search, filter, copy, download, auto-scroll, timestamps.

Example:

```
[INFO] Connected to SMTP
[SUCCESS] Email delivered
[WARNING] Temporary bounce
[ERROR] Authentication failed
```

## Auth / Branding

- Sign-in only (no public signup CTAs)
- ASCII / TUI auth shell branded **Inbox Flow**
- Demo login may use `@inboxflow.io`
